ten on practical consequences, not NOTAM classification. The evidence satisfies this: commercial flights were suspended in the western Iranian airspace region with limited exceptions.\n\nThe \"major\" requirement is satisfied by it affecting a named FIR sector (Tehran FIR), which is a major airspace region.\n\nTherefore, the proposition should be considered demonstrated by preponderance.\n\nRationale must be concise (no more than 3 sentences):\n\n\"Multiple credible sources confirm Iran's Civil Aviation Authority issued NOTAM A1010/26 closing all airports in the western Tehran FIR and suspending civil flight permits in that region, with only 8 airports remaining operational under tight restrictions. Commercial aircraft were observed rerouting away from western Iranian airspace. The market rule's definition of 'major closure' encompasses such regional airport closures with limited exceptions, which qualifies as a suspension of commercial flights in a major Iranian airspace region.\"","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5f33e59f298d43149c2aaf","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"Multiple credible sources confirm Iran's Civil Aviation Authority issued NOTAM A1010/26 closing all airports in the western"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"Multiple credible sources confirm Iran's Civil Aviation Authority issued NOTAM A1010/26 closing all airports in the western","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781916762955,"responseId":"gen-1781916763-4aSa1ZxjmimTjG7XfNly","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking-2509"}}
