ve letters.\n- The first letter is always Q to indicate a NOTAM code abbreviation.\n- The second and third letters identify the subject being reported.\n- The fourth and fifth letters identify the status of operation of the subject being reported.\n\nRelevant subject-code entries:\n- Under ATM Airspace Organization: AF = Flight information region (uniform phraseology: fir).\n- Under ATM Airspace Organization: AR = ATS route (uniform phraseology: ats route).\n- Under AGA Facilities and Services: FA = Aerodrome (uniform phraseology: ad).\n\nRelevant status-code entries:\n- Under Limitations: LC = Closed (uniform phraseology: clsd).\n- Under Limitations: LI = Closed to IFR operations.\n- Under Limitations: LV = Closed to VFR operations.\n\nCapture notes: This extract is from the FAA's public international NOTAM Q-code appendix. It is used only to decode the admitted raw NOTAM QFALC, not as evidence of the Iranian event itself.\n\n[defendant] DX-S2 Raw NOTAM A1010/26 text\nTitle: All west Tehran FIR airports are closed except listed airports operating sunrise to sunset, with new CAA permission required for civil IFR passenger flights. - OIIX NOTAM\nPublisher/source: Notamify\nRetrieved: 2026-06-20T00:48:00Z\nURL: https://notamify.com/notams/OIIX/693f2d0f-54d3-433b-8128-49f5475ba269\n\nRelevant captured text:\n- NOTAM: A1010/26\n- Status display: EST; NOTAM inactive on page footer/status area.\n- Classification shown by page: AD Airport Operations.\n- Page summary: All west Tehran FIR airports are closed except listed airports operating sunrise to sunset, with new CAA permission required for civil IFR passenger flights.\n- Period of applicability shown: UTC 2026-05-22 20:46 - 2026-05-25 08:30.\n- Interpretation: All airports in the west part of Tehran FIR are closed except OITR, OIKK, OIAA, OISS, OIYY, OICC, OIGG, and OIAW, which are operational from sunrise to sunset. All previous permissions are suspended for all operators, and new permission must be requested from the CAA for operation of civil IFR passenger flights on these airports.\n\nRaw NOTAM captured:\nA1010/26 NOTAMR A0799/26\nQ)OIIX/QFALC/IV/NBO/A/000/999/\nA)OIIX B)2605222046 C)2605250830EST\nE)REF NOTAM  A0796/26, ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART\nOF TEHRAN FIR ARE CLSD\nEXCEPT OITR, OIKK, OIAA, OISS, OIYY, OICC, OIGG, AND OIAW THAT ARE\nOPERATIONAL FM SUNRISE TO SUNSET (HJ).\nALL PREVIOUS PERMISSIONS ARE SUSPENDED FOR ALL OPERATORS,\nNEW PERMISSION SHALL BE REQUESTED FM CAA FOR OPRATION OF\nCIVIL IFR PASSENGER FLIGHTS ON THESE AIRPORTS.\n\nCapture notes: web.open returned 92 lines. This is a relevant text capture of the page title, status/classification, applicability, interpretation, and raw NOTAM. Notamify is a third-party NOTAM display service, not the Iranian CAA official archive.\n\nSubmitted evidence:\n[plaintiff arguments] Gulf News May 23 report - Iran shuts western airspace (ev_d98e4358b620_submitted-evidence-01-plaintiff-d98e4358b620)\nSource: https://gulfnews.com/world/mena/iran-shuts-western-airspace-amid-fears-of-renewed-us-strikes-1.500550862\nSHA-256: `d98e4358b620708dc4b1efd9b00802556ea276cdaca96fb0c3e964663b873fdb`\nBytes: 1831\nRelevance: Credible reporting that Iran Civil Aviation Organization announced temporary closure of western Iran airspace and suspended civil flight permits in the western sector of Tehran FIR, with only eight airports operating under daylight and per-flight approval restrictions.\n\n[plaintiff arguments] Gulf News May 24 live page extract - Iran restricts western airspace NOTAM (ev_b6a489acc56c_submitted-evidence-02-plaintiff-b6a489acc56c)\nSource: https://gulfnews.com/world/asia/irans-strait-of-hormuz-plan-sparks-fears-of-global-oil-shock-1.500550639\nSHA-256: `b6a489acc56cfec2a3f10d15ff81743a9a5ee4d615dbe8ebe418b8fac12d0137`\nBytes: 1472\nRelevance: Corroborates that Iran Civil Aviation Authority issued a NOTAM restricting operations at most western airports in Tehran FIR until early May 25, with limited daytime flights at eight sites; supports official/Iran-initiated, non-weather, pre-deadline restriction.\n\n[plaintiff arguments] Abdi Media NOTAM A1010/26 extract (ev_4e23315ca668_submitted-evidence-03-plaintiff-4e23315ca668)\nSource: https://abdimedia.net/en/economic/notam\nSHA-256: `4e23315ca6687dc12e250f1446217d69e9dce676ac6e3befdfb9ead6df1005a5`\nBytes: 1652\nRelevance: Provides specific NOTAM code A1010/26, validity dates, listed exceptions, cancellation of previous permissions, and need for new Civil Aviation Organization authorization for IFR passenger flights.\n\n[plaintiff arguments] Indian Express May 23 report - OIIX A1010/26 and eight-airport limits (ev_0e132c49e091_submitted-evidence-04-plaintiff-0e132c49e091)\nSource: https://indianexpress.com/article/world/us-news/iran-closes-airspace-trump-cancels-plans-us-military-strikes-rubio-india-10704692/\nSHA-256: `0e132c49e091c5665250de354b4bbd969405e0802ba686b26460215244fcdaf9`\nBytes: 2368\nRelevance: Independent corroborating report that identifies NOTAM OIIX A1010/26, western Tehran FIR shutdown effective May 22 to May 25, suspension of civil permits, eight operational airports, daylight-only operations, per-flight approval, and rerouting.\n\n[defendant arguments] Notamify raw NOTAM A1010/26 - airport operations closure text (ev_e727676aa10f_submitted-evidence-05-defendant-e727676aa10f)\nSource: https://notamify.com/notams/OIIX/693f2d0f-54d3-433b-8128-49f5475ba269\nSHA-256: `e727676aa10f1d7a3c5e043f7c8293028310a1a2378e0d2c2f02c5fef70cdc5d`\nBytes: 1777\nRelevance: Provides raw NOTAM text and classification for A1010/26. It identifies the notice as AD Airport Operations/QFALC, states all airports in the west part of Tehran FIR are closed except listed airports, and preserves the limited sunrise-sunset and new CAA permission language relevant to whether the event was an airspace/transit closure or an airport-operations restriction.\n\n[defendant surrebuttals] FAA International NOTAM Q-code table extract - QFA aerodrome and LC closed (ev_f5c3c89cf1da_submitted-evidence-06-defendant-f5c3c89cf1da)\nSource: https://www.faa.gov/air_traffic/publications/atpubs/notam_html/appendix_b.html\nSHA-256: `f5c3c89cf1dab2c5a8b9b048febe0cbadf27fe4dfe35afe667d4852f4aedf48c`\nBytes: 1275\nRelevance: Helps interpret the raw NOTAM code QFALC in A1010/26. The FAA international NOTAM Q-code table states that second/third letters identify the subject, FA means Aerodrome, fourth/fifth letters identify operational status, and LC means Closed; it also distinguishes airspace subjects such as AF Flight Information Region and AR ATS route.\n\nTechnical reports:\n[plaintiff] Source Search And Provenance Assessment\nSearch path: case packet rule text, then web searches for May 24 2026 Iran airspace closure, Iran Civil Aviation Organization, western Tehran FIR, and NOTAM terms. Source material captured and admitted from Gulf News, Abdi Media, and Indian Express. The original official NOTAM archive was not captured; weight rests on consistent reporting that identifies OIIX/A1010/26, issuing aviation authority, dates, FIR scope, exceptions, and security rationale. Adverse issue preserved: eight airports remained available only under daylight/per-flight approval terms, so plaintiff relies on the major-region closure prong rather than the two-listed-airport complete-suspension prong.\n\n[defendant] Defense Source Search And Scope Analysis\nSearched exact NOTAM identifiers and official-domain queries for A1010/26/OIIX. No direct Iranian CAA archive was found in the available time. The submitted Notamify capture preserves the raw NOTAM and classifies it as AD Airport Operations/QFALC; the raw body closes airports in western Tehran FIR except listed airports and permits civil IFR passenger flights with new CAA authorization. This supports a scope distinction between an airport-operations restriction and a broad commercial airspace/transit closure.\n\n[plaintiff] Rebuttal Assessment Of DX-1\nExact read of defendant evidence ev_e727676aa10f shows NOTAM A1010/26 for OIIX/Tehran FIR: all airports in the west part of Tehran FIR closed except listed airports operating sunrise-sunset; all previous permissions suspended for all operators; new CAA permission required for civil IFR passenger flights. Plaintiff treats this as corroboration of a broad regional commercial-flight suspension with limited exceptions allowed by the market rule, while acknowledging it does not prove the separate two-listed-airport complete-suspension prong.\n\n[defendant] Targeted Surrebuttal NOTAM-Code Check\nPlaintiff argued QFALC/AD Airport Operations should not affect the market-rule analysis. A targeted FAA Q-code check found that international NOTAM Q-code second/third letters identify the subject and fourth/fifth identify status; FA means aerodrome, AF means flight information region, AR means ATS route, and LC means closed. This supports reading A1010/26 as an aerodrome-closed NOTAM rather than a FIR or ATS-route closure.\n\nCall submit_council_vote with vote=demonstrated or vote=not_demonstrated.\nKeep the rationale brief: no more than three sentences.\n\nCouncil API instructions:\nYou are a council member. Decide the proposition from the admitted record.\nYou may examine admitted evidence through read-only tools when exact bytes, metadata, or exhibit contents matter.\nDo not search the web, introduce new facts, create new evidence, or upload evidence.\nWhen ready, call submit_council_vote exactly once with vote=demonstrated or vote=not_demonstrated and a concise rationale.\n","state":"ready","status":"ready","tools":[{"description":"Return the current visible arbitration record for this council member.","input_schema":{"additionalProperties":false,"properties":{},"type":"object"},"name":"get_case","read_only":true},{"description":"List visible immutable record evidence.","input_schema":{"additionalProperties":false,"properties":{},"type":"object"},"name":"list_evidence","read_only":true},{"description":"Return metadata and read limits for one visible evidence item.","input_schema":{"additionalProperties":false,"properties":{"evidence_id":{"type":"string"}},"required":["evidence_id"],"type":"object"},"name":"stat_evidence","read_only":true},{"description":"Read a bounded byte range from one visible evidence item as base64.","input_schema":{"additionalProperties":false,"properties":{"evidence_id":{"type":"string"},"length":{"minimum":1,"type":"integer"},"offset":{"minimum":0,"type":"integer"}},"required":["evidence_id","offset","length"],"type":"object"},"name":"read_evidence_range","read_only":true},{"description":"Submit one council vote for the current deliberation opportunity.","input_schema":{"additionalProperties":false,"properties":{"rationale":{"type":"string"},"vote":{"enum":["demonstrated","not_demonstrated"],"type":"string"}},"required":["vote","rationale"],"type":"object"},"name":"submit_council_vote","read_only":false}],"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":false,"deadline":"2026-06-20T01:07:29.713489418Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C5","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C5","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":886778,"role_id":"council","turn_number":13},"wait":{"reason":"ready","state_version":19,"version":29}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"wait_for_opportunity"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781916762949},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to analyze the case arb-ex11a-20260620003004 and determine whether the proposition \"By May 24, 2026, 11:59 PM ET, Iran initiated a major non-weather closure of its airspace within the meaning of the market rule\" is demonstrated or not by preponderance of evidence.\n\nFirst, let's understand the record:\n\n- Rule text in PX-1: A \"major closure\" is defined as a broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian Airspace region. A qualifying closure must apply generally to flights across Iran or a major Iranian airspace region. Limited cancellations, delays, or other partial closures will not qualify. Limited exceptions to a broad closure, however, will not disqualify such a closure from counting (e.g. exceptions for certain flights pre-approved by the Iranian Civil Aviation Authority may be permitted).\n\nAny non-weather complete suspension of commercial arrivals and departures affecting at least two of the following airports will qualify: Imam Khomeini International Airport (IKA), Mehrabad Airport (THR), Mashhad International Airport (MHD), Shiraz International Airport (SYZ), or Isfahan International Airport (IFN).\n\nKey evidence:\n\nPlaintiff evidence:\n- PX-2: Gulf News May 23 report says \"Iran Civil Aviation Organization announced the temporary closure of airspace over western Iran\", \"all civil flight permits had been suspended at airports located in the western sector of Tehran's Flight Information Region\", \"only eight airports across the country remain operational... restricted to daylight hours between sunrise and sunset... fresh approval from the Civil Aviation Organization for each individual flight\"\n\n- PX-3: Gulf News NOTAM restriction live-page extract says \"Iran's Civil Aviation Authority has issued a NOTAM restricting operations at most western airports in the Tehran Flight Information Region until early Monday, May 25, allowing limited daytime flights at eight specific sites\"\n\n- PX-4: Abdi Media NOTAM A1010/26 extract says \"NOTAM with code A1010/26, all airports in the western part of the Tehran FIR are closed, and only a few specified airports are allowed limited operations, and even then only from sunrise to sunset\", \"all previous flight permissions have been canceled, and airlines must obtain new authorization from the Civil Aviation Organization to conduct IFR passenger flights\", valid \"from Friday, May 22, 2026, at 00:16 Iran time to Monday, May 25, 2026, at 12:00 noon Iran time\"\n\n- PX-5: Indian Express report says \"Iran has temporarily closed the airspace over its western half from May 22 to May 25, suspending all civil flight permits in the western sector of the Tehran Flight Information Region (OIIX)\", \"Only eight airports across the country remain operational... flights are restricted to daylight hours from sunrise to sunset, and airlines must obtain fresh per-flight approval from the Civil Aviation Authority\"\n\nDefendant evidence:\n- DX-1: Same as PX-1, the market rule text\n\n- DX-2: Notamify raw NOTAM A1010/26 text says \"Classification shown by page: AD Airport Operations\", \"All airports in the west part of Tehran FIR are closed except OITR, OIKK, OIAA, OISS, OIYY, OICC, OIGG, and OIAW, which are operational from sunrise to sunset. All previous permissions are suspended for all operators, and new permission must be requested from the CAA for operation of civil IFR passenger flights on these airports.\"\n\n- DX-S1: FAA International NOTAM Q-code table extract shows QFALC decodes as Q(=NOTAM) F(=Airport?) A(=Airport?) L(=Closed) C(=Closed), with FA being \"Aerodrome\", and LC being \"Closed\"\n\n- DX-S2: Raw NOTAM text: Q)OIIX/QFALC/IV/NBO/A/000/999/ A)OIIX B)2605222046 C)2605250830EST E)REF NOTAM A0796/26, ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART OF TEHRAN FIR ARE CLSD EXCEPT OITR, OIKK, OIAA, OISS, OIYY, OICC, OIGG, AND OIAW THAT ARE OPERATIONAL FM SUNRISE TO SUNSET (HJ). ALL PREVIOUS PERMISSIONS ARE SUSPENDED FOR ALL OPERATORS, NEW PERMISSION SHALL BE REQUESTED FM CAA FOR OPRATION OF CIVIL IFR PASSENGER FLIGHTS ON THESE AIRPORTS.\n\nKey observations:\n\n- The rule does not require a nationwide airspace closure, but specifically allows \"a broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian airspace region.\"\n\n- The evidence shows a regional closure in western Tehran FIR, affecting many airports with only 8 airports remaining operational under strict daylight/per-flight approval conditions.\n\n- The NOTAM code analysis shows QFALC means Airport Closed (FA=Aerodrome, LC=Closed), not a Flight Information Region or ATS route closure. This suggests it's an airport-specific closure rather than airspace closure.\n\n- However, the rule also says \"a major Iranian airspace region\" qualifies, and a notam affecting multiple airports in a region could constitute closure of that region.\n\n- PX-4 and PX-5 explicitly state \"western Tehran FIR\" or \"western half of Iranian airspace\" was closed, which is a major regional closure.\n\n- The evidence shows suspension of all civil flight permits in the western sector of Tehran FIR, with only limited exceptions. Flight-tracking data shows commercial aircraft rerouting away from western Iranian airspace.\n\nThe key question is whether the \"closure of all airports in west part of Tehran FIR\" (with exceptions) qualifies as \"a broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from [a major] Iranian airspace region.\"\n\nThe rule's definition explicitly includes \"limited exceptions to a broad closure\" as not disqualifying, which matches this scenario (only 8 airports operational with strict limitations).\n\nThe NOTAM classification as \"Airport Operations\" is important, but the rule doesn't define \"major closure\" by NOTAM classification. The rule defines it by consequence: suspension of commercial flights in a region.\n\nIn reality, closing all airports in a FIR region effectively suspends commercial flights transiting, arriving and departing from that region, even if some airports remain with restricted operations.\n\nPX-5 specifically mentions \"commercial aircraft already rerouting away from western Iranian airspace\" - this indicates the effect on transit flights.\n\nThe defense's counter-argument that it's merely an airport-operations closure rather than airspace closure is technically accurate, but the rule does not distinguish this way. The rule explicitly says \"a broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian airspace region\" - and by closing the airports, Iran caused this effect for the region.\n\nThe rule is written on practical consequences, not NOTAM classification. The evidence satisfies this: commercial flights were suspended in the western Iranian airspace region with limited exceptions.\n\nThe \"major\" requirement is satisfied by it affecting a named FIR sector (Tehran FIR), which is a major airspace region.\n\nTherefore, the proposition should be considered demonstrated by preponderance.\n\nRationale must be concise (no more than 3 sentences):\n\n\"Multiple credible sources confirm Iran's Civil Aviation Authority issued NOTAM A1010/26 closing all airports in the western Tehran FIR and suspending civil flight permits in that region, with only 8 airports remaining operational under tight restrictions. Commercial aircraft were observed rerouting away from western Iranian airspace. The market rule's definition of 'major closure' encompasses such regional airport closures with limited exceptions, which qualifies as a suspension of commercial flights in a major Iranian airspace region.\"","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5f33e59f298d43149c2aaf","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"Multiple credible sources confirm Iran's Civil Aviation Authority issued NOTAM A1010/26 closing all airports in the western Tehran FIR and suspending civil flight permits in that region. Commercial aircraft rerouted away from western Iranian airspace. The market rule encompasses regional airport closures with limited exceptions as major airspace closure.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking","usage":{"input":19197,"output":1810,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21007,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781916762955,"responseId":"gen-1781916763-4aSa1ZxjmimTjG7XfNly","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking-2509"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_5f33e59f298d43149c2aaf","toolName":"mcp","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C5\ncase_id: arb-ex11a-20260620003004\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C5\nremaining_ms: 874546\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex11a-20260620003004\",\"member_id\":\"C5\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-20T01:07:29.713489418Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C5\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C5\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":874546,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":13}}"}],"details":{"mode":"call","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C5\ncase_id: arb-ex11a-20260620003004\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C5\nremaining_ms: 874546\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex11a-20260620003004\",\"member_id\":\"C5\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-20T01:07:29.713489418Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C5\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C5\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":874546,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":13}}"}],"structuredContent":{"case_id":"arb-ex11a-20260620003004","member_id":"C5","ok":true,"result":{"text":"Council vote accepted."},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":true,"deadline":"2026-06-20T01:07:29.713489418Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C5","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C5","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":874546,"role_id":"council","turn_number":13}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"submit_council_vote"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1781916775173},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I have successfully cast my vote. Now I need to report that my vote was accepted and stop.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"My council vote was accepted. The proposition has been determined as demonstrated based on the admitted evidence."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking","usage":{"input":19530,"output":43,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19573,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781916775174,"responseId":"gen-1781916775-PHU38z59A1iECnqsjvVr","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-thinking-2509"}],"willRetry":false}
